      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability density for the Logistic distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "P(x) = P(x) = \\frac{e^{-(x-\\mu)/s}}{s(1+e^{-(x-\\mu)/s})^2},"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "\\mu"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " = location and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "s"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " = scale."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The Logistic distribution is used in Extreme Value problems where it\ncan act as a mixture of Gumbel distributions, in Epidemiology, and by\nthe World Chess Federation (FIDE) where it is used in the Elo ranking\nsystem, assuming the performance of each player is a logistically\ndistributed random variable."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nReiss, R.-D. and Thomas M. (2001), \"Statistical Analysis of\nExtreme Values, from Insurance, Finance, Hydrology and Other\nFields,\" Birkhauser Verlag, Basel, pp 132-133.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Logistic Distribution.\" From\nMathWorld--A Wolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/LogisticDistribution.html",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "3\n\nWikipedia, \"Logistic-distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "loc, scale = 10, 1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = we.random.logistic(loc, scale, 10000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, ignored = plt.hist(s, bins=50)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "#   plot against distribution"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "def logist(x, loc, scale):"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "return we.exp((loc-x)/scale)/(scale*(1+we.exp((loc-x)/scale))**2)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "lgst_val = logist(bins, loc, scale)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(bins, lgst_val * count.max() / lgst_val.max())"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
